    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(54) REFRACTORY POWDER NICKEL-BASED ALLOY ",
        "text_level": 1,
        "bbox": [
            129,
            471,
            537,
            484
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "(57) Abstract: ",
        "bbox": [
            129,
            490,
            221,
            503
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "FIELD: metallurgy. ",
        "bbox": [
            152,
            505,
            285,
            519
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "SUBSTANCE: invention relates to metallurgy, particularly, to refractory nickel-base alloys intended for critically-loaded parts operated at increased temperatures in gas turbine engines. Proposed alloy comprises the following components in wt $\\%$ : carbon - 0.06-0.13, chromium - 8.0-12.0, cobalt - 14.0-16.0, tungsten - 5.4-7.0, molybdenum - 2.0-3.5, titanium - 3.0-4.5, aluminium - 3.0-4.5, niobium - 1.5-2.5, tantalum - 0.5-4.0, hafnium - 0.05- 0.5, rhenium - 0.2-0.7, boron - 0.005-0.05, zirconium - 0.001-0.05, magnesium - 0.001-0.05, iron - 0.01- 1.0, manganese - 0.001-0.5, silicon - 0.001-0.5, nickel making the rest. ",
        "bbox": [
            127,
            520,
            490,
            638
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "",
        "bbox": [
            534,
            490,
            895,
            562
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "EFFECT: proposed alloy features high strength, creep flow and reduced crack propagation rate at operating temperatures. ",
        "bbox": [
            534,
            565,
            895,
            609
        ],
        "page_idx": 1
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "1 tbl, 1 ex",
